title: PML-N’s Usama Sarwar wins NA-51 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PMLN)’ candidate, Raja Usama Sarwar has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-51, Murree-cum-Rawalpindi by securing 149,250 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate, Muhammad Latasib Satti who bagged 113,843 votes.
The voters’ turn-out remained 52.49%.
